      <div type="doc" xml:id="CMS1798-01-08-toFrancesSedgwickWatsonF-001">
        <bibl>
          <date type="creation" when="1798-01-08"/>
          <author>Catharine Maria Sedgwick</author>
          <recipient>watson-frances</recipient>
          <head>Catharine Maria Sedgwick to Frances Sedgwick Watson</head>
          <editor>Patricia Kalayjian, Lucinda Damon Bach, Deborah Gussman</editor>
          <edition>CMSOL</edition>
          <name type="transcriber">Patricia Kalayjian</name>
          <date type="transcription" when="2020-09-21"/>
          <subject>Sedgwick Family Relations</subject>
          <subject>Leisure Activities</subject>
          <subject>Children/Childhood</subject>
        </bibl>
        <div type="docbody">
          <opener>
            <dateline>1798/Jan 8</dateline>
            <salute>My Dear Sister</salute>
          </opener>
          <p>I now sit Down to answer Your kind tellers <ptr
              target="CMS1798-01-08-toFrancesSedgwickWatsonF-001-fn1"/> which you wrote me by
            <persRef ref="ingersoll-jonathan">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Ingarsall</persRef> there is A yanky
            baall on thursday next I hope you will be here to attend <unclear>Several?] of them.
              tell <persRef ref="sergeant-elizabeth">cousin betsy</persRef> that she must bring
                <gap/><unclear cert="low">clothes</unclear> to go will you be So kind as to give the
              inclosed to <persRef ref="sedgwick-charles">Charles</persRef> give my love to the Reste of the
              family and except it yourself Tell Brother <persRef ref="sedgwick-theodore2">Theodore</persRef> that
                <gap/><unclear>I will</unclear> anser his letter the next <gap/>
              [opportunity</unclear></p>

          <!-- scan is missing page 2-->
          <p>Miss frances <ptr target="CMS1798-01-08-toFrancesSedgwickWatsonF-001-fn2"/></p>

          <closer>
            <salute>your affectionate </salute>
            <signed>Sister Catharine M Sedgwick</signed>
          </closer>
        </div>
        <div type="docback">
          <note type="source">
            <note type="doctype">
              <p>Letter</p>
            </note>
            <note type="repository">
              <p>Massachusetts Historical Society</p>
            </note>
            <note type="collection">
              <p>Catharine Maria Sedgwick I</p>
            </note>
            <note type="condition">
              <p>Tears and smudges. Address is in another hand, possibly Sedgwick's elder sister,
                Eliza Sedgwick Pomeroy.</p>
            </note>
            <note type="address">
              <p>M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Pamela Sedgwick/Stockbridge</p>
            </note>
            <note type="notation">
              <p>E. M. Pomeroy/1798</p>
            </note>
            <note type="notation">
              <p>For Aunt Kitty</p>
            </note>
          </note>
          <note type="fn" xml:id="CMS1798-01-08-toFrancesSedgwickWatsonF-001-fn1">
            <p>Sedgwick doubtless meant "letters"; she probably accidentally crossed the first l,
              making it a t, and left the two central ts uncrossed so they look like ls.</p>
          </note>
          <note type="fn" xml:id="CMS1798-01-08-toFrancesSedgwickWatsonF-001-fn2">
            <p>In her early letters, Sedgwick frequently enters the name of her recipient in the
              same area as her closing and signature.</p>
          </note>
        </div>
      </div>
